data.title: 30 most famous people from Nebraska and what they are known for
data.meta_description: Who are the most famous people from Nebraska? The region is renowned for its attractive sites and vibrant culture. Learn about famous people from this region.
data.text:
Nebraska is famous for its thriving music scene, vast prairies, spacious farmlands, and fascinating attractions. For many, the region is an ideal spot for a vacation and to explore its fantastic scenery, museums and much more. On top of these, Nebraska is home to incredible talent, and you will be surprised by the sheer number of renowned personalities that hail from this place. So, who are the most famous people from Nebraska?

Nebraska is home to great talent. There are numerous historical figures from Nebraska, and the region still produces incredibly talented people who become famous. How many do you know?

Famous people from Nebraska and what made them

No matter where you come from, you are bound for greatness if you are talented enough and put in the right effort in your career. History has proven that origin doesn’t matter regarding success but how well you utilize the opportunities present.

However, the amount of successful people hailing from Nebraska skews this ideology because of the sheer number. So, what famous people come from Nebraska and what put them in the limelight?

1. Clayton Anderson

Clayton Anderson is a retired NASA astronaut. He was born on February 23, 1959, in Omaha, Nebraska, the United States of America. In 2022, Clayton Anderson became the president and CEO of the Strategic Air Command & Aerospace Museum in his hometown of Ashland.

2. Fred Astaire

Although he died in June 1987, Fred Astaire’s legend lives on. He was a dancer, actor, singer, choreographer and presenter. Fred was born in Omaha, Nebraska on May 10, 1989.

3. Warren Buffet

Warren Buffet is likely the most famous person from Nebraska. He is an American business magnate, investor, and philanthropist. Warren is one of the most influential investors in the world today, with a net worth of $120 billion as of 2023.

4. Wade Boggs

Wade Boggs was born in Omaha, Nebraska in 1958. He is a former American professional baseball third baseman who spent eighteen seasons in Major League Baseball, mostly with the Boston Red Sox. The retired player became the 23rd player to reach 3,000 career hits.

5. Cavett

Cavett is an American television personality and former talk show host. He became famous as a cerebral late-night television host. The TV presenter hails from Gibbon, Nebraska.

6. Vice President Cheney

Did you know Vice President Cheney was born in Lincoln, Nebraska? He's the most famous politician from Nebraska. Nick was the 46th Vice President of the United States of America under George W. Bush (January 20, 2002 – January 20, 2009).

7. Marlon Brando

Marlon Brando was an American actor and activist. He was active in the entertainment industry from 194 to 2004. Marlon is considered one of the most talented actors of the 20th century because of his impeccable talent.

8. Johnny Carson

Although Johnny Carson was born in Corning, Iowa, he was raised in Norfolk, Nebraska. His family moved to the region when he was eight years old, and it was here that he developed his talent for entertaining. Johnny died on January 23, 2005. He was a television host, comedian, writer and producer.

9. Chip Davis

Chip Davis is one of the most famous singers from Nebraska. He is the founder and lead singer of the music group Mannheim Steamroller. Davis moved to Omaha, Nebraska, in the 1970s as he was creating a foundation for his career.

10. Adam DeVine

Adam Devine graduated from Millard South High School in Omaha, Nebraska. Other than this, he doesn’t have any other connection to Nebraska. Adam is an actor, comedian, singer, screenwriter, and producer. Adam is one of the stars and co-creators of the Comedy Central show Workaholics and Adam DeVine’s House Party.

11. David Doyle, a.k.a. Bosley

David Doyle gained fame by portraying John Bosley in the 1970s TV series Charlie’s Angels. He was born on December 1, 1929, and died on February 26, 1997. David also gained fame for voicing Grandpa Lou on the Nicktoon Rugrats.

12. Nicholas D'Agosto

Nicholas is one of the most famous actors from Nebraska. He is renowned for his role sin Final Destination 5, Heroes, and The Office.

13. Farrah Abraham

Farrah Abraham joins the list of famous people from Nebraska because she hails from Omaha. She is a popular reality television personality, singer, actress and writer. Farrah Abraham gained international fame after appearing on the TV series 16 and Pregnant in 2009. The TV show documented the pregnancies of several young women.

14. Samantha Ware

Samantha Ware gained notoriety in the movie industry after she played Jane Hayward in the sixth season of Glee. On top of this, Samantha played Angela Archer in the Netflix series What/If (2019).

15. Ashley Graham

Ashley Graham is an American plus-sized model and TV presenter. She gained fame after her debut in the Sports Illustrated Issue in 2016. Ashley is also an author, and she published her first book in 2016 called A New Model: What Confidence, Beauty, and Power Really Look Like.

16. Nicholas Sparks

Nicholas Sparks was born in Omaha, Nebraska. He is an American romance novelist, screenwriter, and film producer. Nicholas has published twenty-three novels, all New York Times best sellers.

17. Janine Turner

Janine Turner is an American actress who hails from Lincoln, Nebraska. She is best known for playing Maggie in the TV series Northern Exposure and Jessie Deighan in the feature film Cliffhanger.

18. Scott Porter

Scott Potter is an occasional singer and actor known for acting as Jason Street in the NBC television drama Friday Night Lights. He comes from Omaha, Nebraska. Scott has been active in the entertainment industry since 2004 and is married to Kelsey Mayfield (married in 2013).

19. Gabrielle Union

Most people are unaware that Gabrielle Union hails from Omaha, Nebraska. The American actress started her career in the early 90s and has been active in the movie industry for over two decades, making dozens of appearances on TV shows and movies.

20. Marg Helgenberger

Marg hails from Fremont, Nebraska. She is an American actress who gained national attention after playing the role of Siobhan Ryan on the daytime soap opera Ryan’s Hope from 1982 to 1986. Marg Helgenberger has been in the movie industry since 1977, participating in various big and small-budget productions.

21. Emily Kinney

Although Emily Kinney isn’t the most famous person from Nebraska, she is popular in her might. She is an actress, singer and songwriter. Elimy is known for her role as Beth Green on AMC's horror drama show, The Walking Dead.

22. Swoosie Kurtz

Swoosie Kurtz was born on September 6, 1944, in Omaha, Nebraska, in the United States of America. She is an Emmy Award-winning actress. Swoosie made her professional debut in 1975 in the 1975 revival of Ah.

23. Larry the Cable Guy (Daniel Lawrence Whitney)

Daniel Lawrence, popularly known as "Larry the Cable Guy”, hails from Pawnee City, Nebraska. He is a stand-up comedian and was one of the members of the Blue Collar Comedy Tour.

24. Conor Oberst

Conor is a singer and songwriter famous for Bright Eyes. He was born in Omaha, Nebraska on February 15, 1980. Conor has played in various bands, including Desaparecidos, the Faint (previously named Norman Bailer), Commander Venus, Park Ave., Conor Oberst and the Mystic Valley Band, Monsters of Folk, and Better Oblivion Community Center.

25. Tom Osborne

Tom Osborne gained fame while playing American football, but he is retired. He has worked as a coach, serving as head football coach of the Nebraska Cornhuskers from 1973 to 1997.

26. Alexander Payne

Alexander Payne is an American film director, screenwriter, and producer. He is famous for the movies Citizen Ruth (1996), Election (1999), About Schmidt (2002), Sideways (2004), The Descendants (2011), Nebraska (2013) and Downsizing (2017).

27. Andy Roddick

Andy Riddick is a retired professional tennis player. During his time in the game, Andy won the 2003 U.S. Open. He is married to Brooklyn Decker, a swimsuit model and actress.

28. Elliott Smith

Steven Paul Smith, known professionally as Elliott Smith, comes from Omaha, Nebraska. He is an American musician and songwriter.

29. Hilary Swank

Hilary Swank is an actress and film producer. She hails from Lincoln, Nebraska and was born on July 30, 1974. Hilary is renowned for her role on the TV series Camp Wilder.

30. Jorge Garcia

Jorge Garcia is an actor and comedian. He was born in Omaha, Nebraska, on April 28, 1973, and attended the University of California, Los Angeles. Jorge gained fame with his performance as Hector Lopez on Becker.

Final word on famous people from Nebraska

The list of famous people from Nebraska can be longer as immense talent comes from this well-endowed region. This collection shows just how diverse the American entertainment industry is.
